# we will work on data preperation and choosing the right features that will be used
delays_over_time= df_8.drop(['UniqueCarrier','ArrDelay'],axis=1).groupby(['Year','Month']).sum().reset_index()
delays_over_time = pd.melt(delays_over_time, id_vars=['Year','Month'], value_vars=['CarrierDelay', 'WeatherDelay',"NASDelay",'SecurityDelay','LateAircraftDelay'])

#Converting the numbers to months and years
delays_over_time['date'] = delays_over_time['Year'].astype(str) +"_" +delays_over_time['Month'].astype(str)
delays_over_time = delays_over_time.drop(['Year','Month'], axis=1)

#Starting the Visualization Process
plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.title('Delay type trends over time')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
sb.lineplot(x='date', y='value', hue='variable', data=delays_over_time)
plt.show()

If we looked to this chart we will find that the weather conditions delay has no main diffenece between the winter and summer.

In [21]:
#Choosing the right used features
tot_delays = df_8['WeatherDelay'].sum() + df_8['CarrierDelay'].sum()+df_8['SecurityDelay'].sum()+df_8['NASDelay'].sum()+df_8['LateAircraftDelay'].sum()

#MAking the calculations
wd = (df_8['WeatherDelay'].sum())/tot_delays
cd = (df_8['CarrierDelay'].sum())/tot_delays
sd = (df_8['SecurityDelay'].sum())/tot_delays
nd = (df_8['NASDelay'].sum())/tot_delays
ld = (df_8['LateAircraftDelay'].sum())/tot_delays
delay_ratios = [wd,cd,sd,nd,ld]
In [22]:
#Make the visualization
lab = ['Weather Delays','Carrier Delays' , 'NAS Delays', 'Secuirity Delays','Late Air Craft']
plt.pie(delay_ratios,labels = lab, autopct='%.2f%%');
